---
import BlogPostLayout from '../../../layouts/BlogPostLayout.astro';

const title = "Halo Wars 2 Review After 1,000 Hours";
const description = "A comprehensive review of Halo Wars 2 after playing for over 1,000 hours. Discover the pros, cons, and whether this RTS is worth your time in 2026.";
const category = "Reviews";
const publishedDate = "February 2, 2026";
const dateIso = "2026-02-02";
const tags = ["Halo Wars 2"];
const ogImage = "/content/blog/reviews-placeholder.svg";
---

<BlogPostLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  category={category}
  publishedDate={publishedDate}
  dateIso={dateIso}
  ogImage={ogImage}
  tags={tags}
  youtubeId="74TM5X3jgTk"
>
  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
    After playing Halo Wars 2 for well over 1,000 hours (likely closer to 2,000-3,000 hours), including early access before the game launched, this is a comprehensive review of the game roughly five and a half years after release.
  </p>

  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">Short Answer</strong>: Wholeheartedly recommend Halo Wars 2. It's one of the best RTS games ever and a personal favorite of all time.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300">PROS</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Easy to Learn</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Limited base building slots reduce complexity</li>
    <li>Once your base is built, you have a limited number of building slots for economy or production</li>
    <li>Forgiving RTS - mistakes don't immediately end matches like in StarCraft</li>
    <li>Mid-game mistakes can hurt your chances, but overall it's more forgiving</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Low Skill Floor, High Skill Ceiling</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Easy for new players to pick up and play</li>
    <li>Can fit in with players at your skill level</li>
    <li>High skill ceiling for those wanting to master micro and macro</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Unit Variety</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Much more variety than Halo Wars 1</li>
    <li>Different units with unique abilities and functionalities</li>
    <li>Each leader has unique unit compositions</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Accessibility</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Available on Xbox One, Xbox Series consoles, PC, mobile phones, Game Pass, and cloud streaming</li>
    <li>Can play without any hardware via cloud streaming</li>
    <li>Xbox Play Anywhere title</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Content</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Three Campaigns</strong>: Main campaign, Awakening the Nightmare (Banished campaign), Operation Spearbreaker</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Two Firefight Modes</strong>: Blitz Firefight and Terminus Firefight</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Standard Multiplayer</strong>: Team War (unranked 2s and 3s), ranked 2s, ranked 3s, solo ranked</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Blitz Mode</strong>: Card-collecting game mode</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">16 Leaders</strong>: Significant increase from Halo Wars 1's six leaders</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Cross-Play</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Play with friends regardless of platform (PC, Xbox console)</li>
    <li>Mix and match platforms easily</li>
    <li>Possible to even play against cloud streamers or mobile players</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Control Schemes</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Controller and mouse/keyboard support</li>
    <li>Controller is the recommended way to play</li>
    <li>Top-level players use controller - designed with controller in mind</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Semi-Moddable</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Possible to mod the game (e.g., playing as the Flood)</li>
    <li>Videos available showing modding possibilities</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Active Player Base</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Still active online player base</li>
    <li>Can find matches in under 30 seconds at any time of day</li>
    <li>Game is not dead despite claims</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Game Pass Included</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Can access via Game Pass (very cheap entry point)</li>
    <li>Makes it highly accessible</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Performance Enhancements</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>FPS boosted on Series consoles</li>
    <li>4K resolution on Xbox One X and Series consoles</li>
    <li>Best performance is on PC</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">CONS</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Toxic Community</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>One of the most toxic communities in online multiplayer</li>
    <li>Opponents send hostile messages after wins</li>
    <li>Content creators sometimes trash talk other creators</li>
    <li>Tournaments can get mean-spirited</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Performance Issues</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Bugs and glitches</li>
    <li>Crashes frequently on Series X and S consoles</li>
    <li>Crashes occur on all platforms but especially on newest Xbox consoles</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">No Developer Support</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>343 gave up on the title</li>
    <li>No more balance updates coming</li>
    <li>No support for glitches or problems</li>
    <li>Abandoned despite still being quite popular</li>
    <li>Arguably still one of the most popular RTS games in the world</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">No Steam Release</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Strange since Halo Wars 1 is on Steam</li>
    <li>Adding HW2 to Steam with cross-play would help the game significantly</li>
    <li>Hope for Steam release is fading over time</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Limited Modding Support</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>More complicated to mod compared to Halo Wars 1</li>
    <li>No official mod support</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Maps</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Maps are generally lacking in quality</li>
    <li>No S-tier maps besides Sentry or Badlands</li>
    <li>Halo Wars 1 has better map variety and content</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">DLC Confusion</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Awakening the Nightmare not included in Season Pass</li>
    <li>Some DLC never goes on sale</li>
    <li>Best to buy Complete Edition for everything</li>
    <li>Confusing for new players trying to purchase content piecemeal</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Final Verdict</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">Should you buy Halo Wars 2?</strong> YES, absolutely.
  </p>

  <p class="mb-4">
    Despite the issues, after thousands of hours of playtime, the game remains a tremendous experience when it works well (which is most of the time). It's just plain old fun to try out and enjoy.
  </p>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">Is it as good as Halo Wars 1?</strong> Uncertain. A comparison review would be needed, but both games have their merits.
  </p>

</BlogPostLayout>
